  "plot": [
    {
      "plot_summary": "In the backdrop of President Bartlet's third State of the Union address, tensions rise as five DEA agents are taken hostage by Colombian rebels. While Bartlet delivers a meticulously crafted speech by Toby, Josh anxiously monitors public reaction through a phone poll. Complicating matters is a personal rift between Bartlet and Abbey as key issues are overlooked in the speech. Meanwhile, romantic tensions rekindle between Josh and pollster Joey Lucas amidst the chaos."
